messages.content: What is the purpose of ComfyUI_Preset_Merger?
ComfyUI_Preset_Merger is used to merge checkpoint models by preset in ComfyUI.
Which node is available in the ComfyUI_Preset_Merger extension?
The 'ModelMergeByPreset' node is available in the ComfyUI_Preset_Merger extension.
In which category can you find the 'ModelMergeByPreset' node in ComfyUI?
The 'ModelMergeByPreset' node can be found in the 'advanced/model_merging' category in ComfyUI.
What type of examples are missing from the documentation of ComfyUI_Preset_Merger?
The documentation of ComfyUI_Preset_Merger is missing sawtooth examples.
The image 'preset_grids' demonstrates sine examples generated using the ComfyUI_Preset_Merger.
How can presets be merged using ComfyUI_Preset_Merger?
Presets can be merged using the 'ModelMergeByPreset' node available in the ComfyUI_Preset_Merger extension.
Is the 'ModelMergeByPreset' node a built-in feature of ComfyUI?
No, the 'ModelMergeByPreset' node is not a built-in feature of ComfyUI. It is available through the ComfyUI_Preset_Merger extension.
